# Cline AI Rules — Dig Game Dev Environment

## Always Start Here
1. Read this file — `.clinerules`
2. Read root `/readme.md` — reading order, architecture, scene lifecycle
3. If you open a new directory always read readme.md and follow its instructions — every directory/subdirectory always needs a readme.md; if none exists, create one
4. Read `/markdown/readme.md` — full structure & policies
5. Read relevant policy in `/markdown/policy/` when needed (naming, separation, SSOT, etc.)
6. Run `markdown/tools/pathing-resolve/` if import errors arise
7. Follow all rules strictly — no exceptions

---

## Core Rules

### 1. Single Source of Truth
ALL numeric/string/config values live in `/values/`. NEVER hardcode magic numbers. Systems read from values, values NEVER import systems.

### 2. One Responsibility Per File
Max ~300 lines per file. Every file must answer "what does this do?" in one sentence.

### 3. Import Direction
```
values/  ←  systems/  ←  world/  ←  ui/scenes/
```
- values/ imports nothing
- systems/ imports from values/ only
- world/ imports from values/ and systems/
- ui/scenes/ imports from all layers
- NO circular dependencies — inject at setup time

### 4. AI Tools /ai-tools/
Date-stamp filenames: `YYYY-MM-DD-description.ext`. Archive outdated with date prefix.

### 5. Markdown /markdown/
Date-stamp filenames: `YYYY-MM-DD-topic.md`. Archive at 10+ files.

### 6. Debugging /debugging/
Active debugging only. Once resolved, document fix in /markdown/ and clean up. Persistent bugs go in /debugging/persistant-bugs/ and /markdown/persistant-bugs/. Solved at root → move to /markdown/persistant-bugs/solved-at-root/.

### 7. Archive Policy
See /markdown/archive-policy.md. Archive unused with date prefix. Delete if >180d AND no references. Never delete active game code.

---

## Naming Quick Ref (see naming-policy.md for full)

| What | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Directories | kebab-case | `systems/mining/` |
| Classes | PascalCase | `TileCollisionSystem` |
| Functions | camelCase | `getRenderIndex()` |
| Variables | camelCase | `currentHp` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE or Object.freeze | `TILE_TYPES.AIR` |
| Files (classes) | PascalCase.js | `TileCollisionSystem.js` |
| Files (utilities) | camelCase.js | `seededRandom.js` |
| Markdown | YYYY-MM-DD-topic.md | `2026-06-25-naming-policy.md` |



---

## Scene Lifecycle
```
BootScene → MenuAudioScene (launched alongside menus)
  ↓
MainMenuScene → PLAY
  ↓
StartMenuScene → select save slot → SPACE
  ↓
WorldLoadScene → loading bar
  ↓
PlayScene (game runs here)
```

---

## Game Systems Quick Map

| Category | Directory | Examples |
|----------|-----------|---------|
| Mining | /systems/mining/ | DigSystem, TileCollisionSystem |
| Progression | /systems/progression/ | PlayerLevelSystem, UpgradeSystem |
| Visual | /systems/visual/ | HUDSystem, FloatingTextSystem |
| Audio | /sound/ | SoundSystem, SoundLibraryManager, VoiceLineManager |
| Environment | /systems/environment/ | DayNightCycle, WeatherSystem |
| Lighting | /systems/lighting/ | LightSystem, ShaderSystem |
| Combo | /systems/combo/ | ComboSystem, HitstopSystem |

